OL,3,CNew football regulator must 'be based
OL,4,Cwhere sport is woven into fabric'
OL,6,FThe creation of the regulator is at
OL,7,Fthe heart of the Football Governance
OL,8,FBill, which is due to undergo its
OL,9,Fsecond reading in the House of Commons.
OL,11,FBury has now been put forward as the
OL,12,Fhome of the regulator by MP James
OL,13,FFrith, who says the "trauma" the town
OL,14,Ffelt "when we faced a no-fan-fault
OL,15,Feviction from the Football League...
OL,16,Fwill never been forgotten".
OL,18,FThe letter is co-signed by Bury South
OL,19,FMP Christian Wakeford and Eamonn
OL,20,FO'Brien, the leader of Bury Council.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/9
