OL,4,Cwhere sport is woven into fabric'
OL,6,FIt also introduced an amendment that
OL,7,Fwould make a club's contribution to
OL,8,Fthe economic and social well-being of
OL,9,Fits local community part of its
OL,10,Fcorporate governance.
OL,12,FAnd ministers indicated the regulator
OL,13,Fcould eventually be expanded to
OL,14,Finclude women's football.
OL,16,FDavid Kogan has been selected as the
OL,17,FGovernment's preferred candidate to
OL,18,Fchair the new regulator.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
